title: PML-N’s Tanveer Aslam Malik wins PP-21 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate, Tanveer Aslam Malik has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-21, Chakwal-II by securing 83,055 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Tariq Mehmood Afzal who bagged 75,142 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 58.75%.
